result.execSummary:
The defendant Barrett C Benhoff was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Barrett C Benhoff is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Barrett C Benhoff was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Barrett C Benhoff was found guilty of Violate No Contact Court Order (Felony Conviction), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.39(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:52 AM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing. Attorney Kristy Gordon in court for State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Barrett C Benhoff in court, in custody at WCJ.  Attorney Peter M Wolff in court for Barrett C Benhoff.  Atty. Wolff advises parties are prepared to proceed to plea and sentencing today and he has filed a plea questionnaire.  State recites the offer.  Atty. Wolff confirms the offer.  Victim rights have been complied with by the Waukesha County District Attorneys Office.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 2 (with the domestic abuse repeater enhancer struck) and 3, Court finds defendant guilty of Counts 2 & 3.  Court will order Count 1 dismissed outright.

Sentencing arguments made by the State.
Victim presents statements.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Wolff.
Defendant presents statements.
Victim presents additional statements.

COUNT 2: 
The Court Orders the Following:

90 Days Jail Straight Time (141 Days Credit - Concurrent to Count 3 and sentence in 19CF1654 Count 1).  Sentence commences forthwith.

COSTS: $343.00 (includes D.A. surcharge);
	
DNA Surcharge: $200.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture: to be paid during term of imprisonment and during extended supervision as ordered in 19CF1654.  Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.



COUNT 3:
The Court Orders the Following:

1 Year Jail Straight Time (141 Days Credit - Concurrent to Count 2 and sentence in 19CF1654 Count 1).  Sentence commences forthwith.

COSTS: $268.00;
	
DNA Surcharge: $250.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture: to be paid during term of imprisonment and during extended supervision as ordered in 19CF1654.  Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.
